<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,289,673]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">
The 
<typeStatus box="[205,308,289,313]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">lectotype</typeStatus>
of this species is from Coimbatore, 
<collectingCountry box="[738,799,289,313]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">India</collectingCountry>
, the species being widespread in that country and also recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[318,421,325,349]" name="Tanzania" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[434,518,325,349]" name="Nigeria" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[573,668,325,349]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[683,954,325,349]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Palmer, J. M. (1981) Identification, distribution and host-plants of the pest species of Scirtothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae). Bulletin of Entomological Research, 71, 467 - 479." type="journal article" year="1981">
Mound &amp; Palmer, 
<number box="[895,954,325,349]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), as well as 
<collectingCountry box="[1093,1223,325,349]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
Islands (zur Strassen, 
<number box="[203,263,361,385]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" value="1993.0">1993</number>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[283,455,361,385]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Anaphothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oligochaetus">
<emphasis box="[283,455,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. oligochaetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is particularly similar in structure to 
<taxonomicName box="[877,967,361,385]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis box="[877,967,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the differences indicated in the key above.
</paragraph>
